cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper focuses on improving the training efficacy of adaptive deep networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes techniques to enhance collaboration among classifiers, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
